# Critical Release Checklist

## Requirement and review evidence

- [ ] Confirmed requirements map to acceptance evidence.
- [ ] Review contract is populated with real invariants and commands.
- [ ] Critical/high findings are resolved or explicitly accepted by an authorized owner.

## Security and data

- [ ] Threat model reviewed for this release.
- [ ] Authorization and tenant-boundary tests pass.
- [ ] Secrets and sensitive logging checks pass.
- [ ] Migration/backfill dry run and reconciliation pass when applicable.
- [ ] Backup and recovery evidence is current.

## Operations

- [ ] Deployment owner and incident owner are available.
- [ ] Dashboards, alerts, and runbooks cover material failure modes.
- [ ] Rollback trigger and procedure are tested or rehearsed.
- [ ] R0 actions have explicit human approval.

## Release

- [ ] Build artifact and configuration are traceable.
- [ ] Post-deployment verification steps are assigned.
- [ ] Residual risks and skipped checks are recorded.
- [ ] `PROJECT_STATE.md` names the release state and next action.
